      "name": "Nominal operating point: 3500 RPM, 4.0 L/min",
      "description": "PIV-measured velocity fields compared against CFD predictions at 3500 RPM and 4.0 L/min. RH index = 0.82. Agreement within 6% across all monitored cross-sections. This operating point represents the design-center condition."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-nominal-3000rpm-4lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal operating point: 3000 RPM, 4.0 L/min",
      "description": "PIV-measured velocity fields and hemolysis bench data compared against CFD at 3000 RPM and 4.0 L/min. RH index = 0.76. Maximum velocity discrepancy 7.1%. Representative of mid-range clinical flow demand."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-03-nominal-2500rpm-3lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal operating point: 2500 RPM, 3.0 L/min",
      "description": "Bench hemolysis measurements compared against CFD-predicted shear exposure at 2500 RPM and 3.0 L/min. RH index = 0.71. Shear stress distributions within 9% of measured values. Represents moderate-demand perfusion scenario."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-04-nominal-3000rpm-5lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal operating point: 3000 RPM, 5.0 L/min",
      "description": "High-flow nominal condition at 3000 RPM and 5.0 L/min. CFD versus bench hemolysis index comparison. RH index = 0.88. Velocity field agreement within 8%. Represents elevated cardiac output demand within normal clinical range."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-05-nominal-2000rpm-2lpm",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Nominal lower-bound operating point: 2000 RPM, 2.0 L/min",
      "description": "Lower-bound nominal condition at 2000 RPM and 2.0 L/min. RH index = 0.68. This point anchors the low end of the validated envelope but does not approach the stall-onset regime (below 1.5 L/min) identified in the COU as clinically critical. Edge cases in the high-shear impeller tip and stall-onset regions were identified as requiring separate investigation; that supplementary study is pending and is not incorporated into this credibility package."
